.\"@ s-bsdipa - create or apply binary difference patch.
.
.Dd May 18, 2026
.ds VV \\%v0.9.1
.ds XX \\%S-BSDIPA
.ds Xx \\%S-bsdipa
.ds xX \\%s-bsdipa
.
.Dt "\*(XX" 1
.Os
.
.
.Sh NAME
.Nm \*(Xx \%[\*(VV]
.Nd create or apply binary difference patch
.
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.
.Nm \*(xX\&32
.Bk
\(em 32-bit limits
.Ek
.Nm \*(xX\&64
.Bk
\(em 64-bit limits
.Ek
.
.Pp
.Nm \*(xX
.Fl h
.
.Pp
.Nm \*(xX
.Op Fl fHJjRtZz1-9
.Ar diff Ns Op /WINDOW
.Ar before
.Ar after
.Ar patch
.
.Pp
.Nm \*(xX
.Op Fl fHJjRZz
.Ar patch
.Ar after
.Ar before
.Ar restored
.
.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.
.Pp
\*(Xx creates or applies binary difference patches
by using Colin Percival's BSDiff algorithm.
Two distinct, non-interchangeable variants exist:
.Nm \*(xX\&32
has 32-bit file size limits,
.Nm \*(xX\&64
64-bit;
memory footprint and control data size of the former is roughly half
that of the latter.
(Operational limit may be furtherly constrained by the address size
limit of the host.)
.
.Pp
When applying a
.Ar patch
the compression method is automatically detected,
an explicitly given one must match.
When creating a differential patch the optional
.Ar WINDOW
allows specification of the
.Dq data inspection window size ,
a positive integral value \[<=]4096 that defaults to 16,
and has impacts on processing speed and patch size.
(Values outside the range 4 to 64 seem hardly useful.)
.
.Ss "Options"
.
.Bl -tag -compact -width ".It Fl BaNg"
.It Fl 1 Ns \0\(em Fl 9
Selects the compression level when supported,
with 1 being weakest and 9 being strongest (default unless noted).
.It Fl f
Overwrite an existing target file.
.It Fl H
Do not read or write file identity header;
one of
.Fl J | j | R | Z | z
must be used in addition.
.It Fl h
Show usage information and exit.
.It Fl J
(Optional)
Use LZMA2 compression (default:
.Fl 8 ) .
.It Fl j
(Optional)
Use bzip2 compression.
.It Fl R
Uncompressed patch format without checksum (for testing).
.It Fl t
(Optional)
Use (textual) line-based instead of (binary) BSDiff mode;
.Ar WINDOW
is unsupported.
.Sy Note:
this mode is not designed to work with malicious data,
there is no protection against "algorithmic complexity attacks";
the output is, however, reproducible, just like the BSDiff one.
.It Fl Z
(Optional)
Use ZSTD compression (default:
.Fl 8 ) .
.It Fl z
Use ZLIB compression (default).
.El
.
.
.Sh AUTHORS
.
.An "Steffen Nurpmeso" Aq steffen@sdaoden.eu .
.
